This paper is about medical image synthesis using generative adversarial networks (GANs). The paper focuses on introducing a sketch prior constraint to guide the medical image generation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to medical image synthesis using GANs, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions various image modalities, including X-Ray, CT, and MRI, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses synthesized images for data augmentation to improve medical image segmentation, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
